   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3178_1.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <address rend="letterhead">
                  <addrLine>The Little Orchard</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Shoreham</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Kent</addrLine>
               </address>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1914-06-10">June 10 |14</date>
               </dateline>

               <salute>My dear friend:</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I stupidly did not realise <choice><abbr>y<hi rend="superscript"
                     >r</hi>.</abbr><expan>your</expan></choice> birthday on the anniversary –, but
               please accept belated, – but <hi rend="underline">very</hi> good wishes for many more
               happy &amp; peaceful birthdays.</p>
            <p>I am settled here, I hope, till the end of July, so hope you will both <pb n="2"
                  facs="uoedh_hl_h.3178_2.jpg"/> come down here some day to luncheon or tea, – or
               both?</p>
            <p>It is only an hour from the <placeName ref="#pl:VictoriaStation">
                  <hi rend="underline"> South Eastern</hi> &amp; <hi rend="underline"
                     >Chatham-Victoria</hi></placeName> – &amp; I am one mile from <placeName
                  ref="#pl:ShorehamKent">Shoreham</placeName> Station.</p>
            <!-- Check this! -->
            <p>I hope you have less trouble with the veins in <choice><abbr>y<hi rend="superscript"
                        >r</hi>.</abbr><expan>your</expan></choice> leg, &amp; that you may <pb
                  n="3" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3178_3.jpg"/> be able to mount a hill near this house, (or
               cottage rather,) &amp; look down upon a really <hi rend="underline">glorious</hi>
               view.</p>
            <p>I wonder what you are now doing in the way of writing? Poetry, perhaps?</p>
            <p>I heard a sad account, a month or so ago, of the terrible poverty &amp; distress in
               which poor <persName ref="#ps:StephenPhillips">Stephen Phillipps</persName> now is.
               He ought to get a pension from the Treasury. –</p>
            <pb n="4" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3178_4.jpg"/>

            <p>I am disgusted with <persName ref="#ps:PrinceArthurofConnaught">Prince A - of
                  Connaught</persName> for opening the new physiological Laboratory at <placeName
                  ref="#pl:UniversityofCambridge">Cambridge</placeName>, &amp; going out of his way
               to identify himself with the worst type of vivisector. - I only wish some mad woman
                        <choice><abbr>w<hi rend="superscript"
                  >d</hi>.</abbr><expan>would</expan></choice> burn down that place! It is awful to
               think of all those "<hi rend="underline">private</hi> research rooms"–. –</p>
            <p>I hope you are getting fond of "Wessex?" Please ask <persName ref="#ps:FlorenceHardy"
                  >Florence</persName> to write to me some day – &amp; tell me all <choice><abbr><hi
                        rend="underline">yr</hi>.</abbr><expan>your</expan></choice> news – my best
               love to her.</p>

            <closer>
               <salute><choice><abbr>Yr</abbr><expan>Your</expan></choice>
                  <choice><abbr>aff.</abbr><expan>affectionate</expan></choice> friend</salute>
               <signed>FH</signed>
            </closer>


         </div>


